# Odometer Feature — Implementation Plan

Users retroactively add trips from PDFs. They can't recall per-trip odometer readings, only checkpoint readings (ITV, taller, seguro). The feature calculates work vs. private km ratio per period for tax compliance (Finanzamt/Hacienda).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This feature is **Pro-only**. Free-tier users will see the section with a lock/upgrade CTA instead of the form.

> [!NOTE]
> Each snapshot includes a **user-uploaded photo** (e.g. photo of the odometer display, ITV paper scan). These photos are the actual proof exported, stored in Supabase Storage bucket `odometer-images`.


---

## Proposed Changes

### Database

#### [NEW] Migration `add_odometer_snapshots`
```sql
CREATE TABLE public.odometer_snapshots (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  snapshot_date DATE NOT NULL,
  reading_km NUMERIC NOT NULL,
  source TEXT,   -- 'itv', 'taller', 'seguro', 'manual', etc.
  notes TEXT,
  image_storage_path TEXT,  -- Storage path of the user-uploaded photo of the odometer
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);
ALTER TABLE public.odometer_snapshots ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "own snapshots" ON public.odometer_snapshots
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id) WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_odometer_user_date ON public.odometer_snapshots(user_id, snapshot_date);
```

Images are stored in a new Supabase Storage bucket: **`odometer-images`** (private, RLS-protected).

---

### Context / Data layer

#### [NEW] `src/contexts/OdometerContext.tsx`
- `useOdometer()` hook
- Fetches `odometer_snapshots` for current user from Supabase
- Exposes: `snapshots`, `addSnapshot()`, `deleteSnapshot()`, `loading`
- Each snapshot: `{ id, snapshot_date, reading_km, source, notes, image_storage_path, extractionStatus }`
- Calculates `computeRatio(startDate, endDate, workKm)` → `{ totalKm, workKm, privateKm, pct }`

